comment: I saw all the aurora features as white, but a few other people I met on the street said they saw them as faintly green (they are about 20 years younger than I am, maybe their eyes are better). As I wrote above, some parts were visible for a longer time and did not appear to move. Others appeared to move, or existed for only a short time. There were some shapes that almost seemed artificial, like two streaks under 90__ angle to each other. It was awesome! I tried to take some photos with my phone but they all failed. And I don't think photos would capture it anyway, the movement and the way they appear and disappear is an important part of the experience. It was awesome!
